import math
for _ in range(int(input())):
    l = list(map(int, input().split()))
    num1 = l[1]
    num2 = l[2]
    g = math.gcd(num1, num2)
    for i in range(3, l[0]):
        g = math.gcd(g, l[i])
    li = l[1:]
    for j in range(len(li)):
        li[j] = li[j] // g
    print(*li)

import math
from functools import reduce
for i in range(int(input())):
    ing = [int(num) for num in input().split()]
    ing.pop(0)
    x = reduce(math.gcd, ing)
    for i in range(len(ing)):
        print(ing[i] // x, end=' ')
    print()

import math
T = int(input())
for i in range(T):
    li = list(map(int, input().split()))
    n = li[0]
    li.remove(li[0])
    gcd = math.gcd(li[0], li[1])
    for j in range(2, n):
        gcd = math.gcd(gcd, li[j])
    for k in range(n):
        li[k] = int(li[k] / gcd)
    print(*li, sep=' ')

from math import gcd
from functools import reduce
t = int(input())
for i in range(t):
    l = list(map(int, input().split()))
    a = len(l)
    l1 = l[1:a]
    x = reduce(gcd, l1)
    for i in l1:
        print(i // x, end=' ')
    print('')
